 The number 2026 lies on the outer ring of the spiral.  
For a point on ring \(n\) at the “first” position \((n,\;-(n-1))\) the eight neighbours are  

\[
\begin{array}{c|c}
\text{Neighbour} & \text{Value} \\ \hline
\text{east}   & (2n+1)^2+2\\
\text{west}   & (2n-1)^2\\
\text{north}  & (2n-1)^2+2\\
\text{south}  & (2n+1)^2\\
\text{northeast} & (2n+1)^2+3\\
\text{northwest} & (2n-3)^2+1\\
\text{southeast} & (2n+1)^2+1\\
\text{southwest} & (2n+1)^2-1
\end{array}
\]

For \(2026\) we have \(n=23\).  Substituting \(n=23\),

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{east}   &= 47^2+2 = 2211\\
\text{west}   &= 45^2 = 2025\\
\text{north}  &= 45^2+2 = 2027\\
\text{south}  &= 47^2 = 2209\\
\text{northeast} &= 47^2+3 = 2212\\
\text{northwest} &= 43^2+1 = 1850\\
\text{southeast} &= 47^2+1 = 2210\\
\text{southwest} &= 47^2-1 = 2208
\end{aligned}
\]

Adding them:

\[
2211+2025+2027+2209+2212+2210+1850+2208 = 16952 .
\]

Hence the sum of the eight neighbours of 2026 is  

\[
\boxed{16952}.
\]
